			<title><![CDATA[January '13 Release Thread]]></title>
			<link>http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?74596-January-13-Release-Thread&amp;goto=newpost</link>
			<pubDate>Mon, 31 Dec 2012 21:44:41 GMT</pubDate>
			<description><![CDATA[I can't say the new year is starting off with a bang, but there are still several titles I am personally excited for. Arguably the "biggest" release of the month is the reboot of Devil May Cry, but the PS3 is also getting an exclusive jrpg years in the making in the form of Ni no Kuni.  
 
When Ni...]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>I can't say the new year is starting off with a bang, but there are still several titles I am personally excited for. Arguably the &quot;biggest&quot; release of the month is the reboot of Devil May Cry, but the PS3 is also getting an exclusive jrpg years in the making in the form of Ni no Kuni. <br />
<br />
When Ni no Kuni was first announced, it's attempt at recreating Studio Ghibili's artistic style was amazing. Graphics have improved enough in general over the years where it is no longer brain melting, but still quite appealing if you are a fan of their work. I've been looking to this one for awhile, but I have quite a few jrpgs I haven't gotten around to playing yet at the moment.<br />
<br />
The DMC remake is being made by Ninja Theory (Enslaved, Heavenly Sword), a company known for good stories but somewhat mediocre combat. Combined with a redesign of the main character, and fans have been complaining since day one. I, however, am optimistic. My dilemma isn't whether or not to get it, but for what platform and for what pricepoint (this sort of game, no matter how good, always seems to drop in price fast).<br />
<br />
I've got a couple runner's up games I want to bring attention to as well. The first is Anarchy Reigns, a game I am not myself supremely hyped for but thought some might like to know about. It's this kind of open arena fighter/brawler based around characters from Mad World, along with having Bayonetta as a DLC character.<br />
<br />
Finally, Kickstarter has had a rather large number of space sim projects announced, but one of them is apparently done. Much like with FTL, the developers of Strike Suit Zero only needed money to finish the game, so it is supposed to come out this month. I believe the game is done in Freespace 2's style, with inspiration from other sources (such as Gundam and Homeworld) making themselves known in various ways. One of the ships you fly is a transformable mech for example. <br />
<br />
I might add some videos later.<br />
<br />
